{"id": "dig1705473594272_2", "title": "Define a Windows Application Shell", "breadcrumbs": ["Developing Desktop Applications", "Application Shells for Desktop Applications", "Define a Windows Application Shell"], "url": "https://docs.rocketsoftware.com/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dig1705473594272_2.html", "html": "<html><body><header class=\"zDocsTopicPageHead\"><h1 class=\"css-g931ng\">Define a Windows Application Shell</h1><div class=\"zDocsTopicActions\" role=\"list\"><div class=\"zDocsBundlePagination\" data-testid=\"next-prev-container\" role=\"listitem\"><div class=\"zDocsPrevTopicButton zDocsPrevTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Previous:  Properties of Windows Application Shells   \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Previous:  Properties of Windows Application Shells   \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zai1705473299234_2.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-prev\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-prev\"></use></svg></a></span></div><div class=\"zDocsNextTopicButton zDocsNextTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Next:   Define a Character Mode Application Shell   \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Next:   Define a Character Mode Application Shell   \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/apf1705474154305_2.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></a></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsMyDocsMenu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Add to My Topics\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Add to My Topics\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" id=\"addToMyDocsDropdownTrigger\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/dig1705473594272_2.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/dig1705473594272_2.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/dig1705473594272_2.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5827591\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5827591\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dig1705473594272_2.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dig1705473594272_2.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dig1705473594272_2.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"btm1665702750753\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define a Windows Application Shell \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Create a Windows shell for Uniface applications that run on any supported Windows platform.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"btm1665702750753__context_w2309ab1b5b1_w2310ab1b5_w2311ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"btm1665702750753__topic_d12497e1_d12498e1_d12499e1\">You must have created a project to contain your\n\t\tapplication definitions. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hkq1665702549855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkq1665702549855.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions.\">Working with Projects</a>.\n                             </div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5765e1_d5766e1_d5767e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the U-Bar, click Browse, select <code class=\"ph codeph\">prj</code>, then choose the project you want to open.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5768e1_d5769e1_d5770e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Templates tab of the Resource Browser, select the Windows Shell template, then drag and drop onto the project object in the Structure.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5771e1_d5772e1_d5773e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"btm1665702750753__p_d12500e1_d12501e1_d12502e1\">Right-click the new application shell and click\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Open</span> to open it in the Application Shell Editor. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Notice that the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Shell Type</span> property is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">APS\n                     (Windows)</code>.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5774e1_d5775e1_d5776e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set the Presentation Properties applicable for your application.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5777e1_d5778e1_d5779e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Enter the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Title Bar Text</span> to be displayed instead of the technical application name. For example <code class=\"ph codeph\">My Application</code> instead of MYAPP.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5780e1_d5781e1_d5782e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you have defined IncludeScripts or global objects, such messages and menus, enter the name of <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Library</span> where they are located.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5783e1_d5784e1_d5785e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you have defined menus or panels, click the More icon (<img alt=\"more\" class=\"image\" id=\"btm1665702750753__image_mfz_qb1_d1c\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/ellipsis.png?_LANG=enus\"/>) in the following properties to browse and select the initial\n                     application menus and panels. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5786e1_d5787e1_d5788e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Menu Bar</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5789e1_d5790e1_d5791e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Pop-up Menu</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5792e1_d5793e1_d5794e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Panel</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5795e1_d5796e1_d5797e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Session Panel</span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"btm1665702750753__note_w2312ab1b5b3b7b3b5b3b3_w2313ab1b5b3b7b3b5b3_w2314ab1b5b3b7b3b5_w2315ab1b5b3b7b3_w2316ab1b5b3b7_w2317ab1b5b3_w2318ab1b5_w2319ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> These properties may be overridden by menus and panels\n                        specified in form components.</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5798e1_d5799e1_d5800e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set the properties applicable for your application window and background color or image.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5801e1_d5802e1_d5803e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"btm1665702750753__p_d12503e1_d12504e1_d12505e1\">In <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Window/App</span>, click\n                     the More icon (<img alt=\"more\" class=\"image\" id=\"btm1665702750753__image_eyd_5b1_d1c\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/ellipsis.png?_LANG=enus\"/>) to open the Define Application Shell Properties dialog.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">The editor displays tabs for Window, Image, and More properties.</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5804e1_d5805e1_d5806e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Window tab, set Window properties, such as the buttons displayed in the title bar.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"btm1665702750753__note_w2320ab1b5b3b9b3b3b3b1_w2321ab1b5b3b9b3b3b3_w2322ab1b5b3b9b3b3_w2323ab1b5b3b9b3_w2324ab1b5b3b9_w2325ab1b5b3_w2326ab1b5_w2327ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> If you define the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Title Bar Text</span> ensure\n                        the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Caption</span> is enabled. Otherwise the text will not\n                        be displayed.</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5807e1_d5808e1_d5809e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Image tab, define a background image for your application window, and set its properties.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5810e1_d5811e1_d5812e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"btm1665702750753__p_d12506e1_d12507e1_d12508e1\">In the More tab, define your own\n                     application properties.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">Click the + icon to insert a property, or - to delete a property.</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5813e1_d5814e1_d5815e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">When you're finished, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span> to save your settings, or <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Cancel</span> to abandon your changes.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5816e1_d5817e1_d5818e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"btm1665702750753__p_d12509e1_d12510e1_d12511e1\">In the script editor, write ProcScript to define\n               the application environment and actions required to initialize the application. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example, use the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">apStart</span> trigger to set the language and library, or open a\n                  database that requires explicit logon information, and activate the first\n                  component.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"btm1665702750753__note_w2328ab1b5b3c11b3b1_w2329ab1b5b3c11b3_w2330ab1b5b3c11_w2331ab1b5b3_w2332ab1b5_w2333ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> At a minimum, the application shell should activate the default form for the application.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"btm1665702750753__p_d12512e1_d12513e1_d12514e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jcj1665702550017.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jcj1665702550017.html\" title=\"System trigger that starts the application environment and controls the interaction of the application with the component manager.\">trigger apStart</a>. </p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5819e1_d5820e1_d5821e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Optionally, write code in other triggers to respond to user events and messages from other components.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5822e1_d5823e1_d5824e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ghq1665702608876.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ghq1665702608876.html\" title=\"Reacts to asynchronous messages that come from outside the application.\">trigger receiveMessage</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5825e1_d5826e1_d5827e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xye1665702608643.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xye1665702608643.html\" title=\"Trigger that responds to a request for a menu in a desktop application.\">trigger menu</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5828e1_d5829e1_d5830e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ppz1665702665163.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ppz1665702665163.html\" title=\"Interactive trigger that defines the application-wide actions in response to the ^SWITCH_KEY action, such as loading a new keyboard translation table.\">trigger keyboardSwitch</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5831e1_d5832e1_d5833e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"niy1665702606431.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/niy1665702606431.html\" title=\"Trigger for responding to user-defined key sequences as defined in the Keyboard Translation Table (KTT) or defined in the usys.ini section named as userkeys.\">trigger userKey</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"btm1665702750753__li_d5834e1_d5835e1_d5836e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span> to compile the application shell.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ohj1705472401504.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Application Shells</a><p>An application shell is a module used to initialize and run an application (Windows or character-based) or application server.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5827591\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5827591\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define a Windows Application Shell Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define a Windows Application Shell Create a Windows shell for Uniface applications that run on any supported Windows platform. You must have created a project to contain your application definitions. For more information, see Working with Projects . In the U-Bar, click Browse, select prj , then choose the project you want to open. In the Templates tab of the Resource Browser, select the Windows Shell template, then drag and drop onto the project object in the Structure. Right-click the new application shell and click Open to open it in the Application Shell Editor. Notice that the Shell Type property is set to APS (Windows) . Set the Presentation Properties applicable for your application. Enter the Title Bar Text to be displayed instead of the technical application name. For example My Application instead of MYAPP. If you have defined IncludeScripts or global objects, such messages and menus, enter the name of Library where they are located. If you have defined menus or panels, click the More icon ( ) in the following properties to browse and select the initial application menus and panels. Menu Bar Pop-up Menu Panel Session Panel Note: These properties may be overridden by menus and panels specified in form components. Set the properties applicable for your application window and background color or image. In Window/App , click the More icon ( ) to open the Define Application Shell Properties dialog. The editor displays tabs for Window, Image, and More properties. In the Window tab, set Window properties, such as the buttons displayed in the title bar. Tip: If you define the Title Bar Text ensure the Caption is enabled. Otherwise the text will not be displayed. In the Image tab, define a background image for your application window, and set its properties. In the More tab, define your own application properties. Click the + icon to insert a property, or - to delete a property. When you're finished, click OK to save your settings, or Cancel to abandon your changes. In the script editor, write ProcScript to define the application environment and actions required to initialize the application. For example, use the apStart trigger to set the language and library, or open a database that requires explicit logon information, and activate the first component. Note: At a minimum, the application shell should activate the default form for the application. For more information, see trigger apStart . Optionally, write code in other triggers to respond to user events and messages from other components. trigger receiveMessage trigger menu trigger keyboardSwitch trigger userKey Click Compile to compile the application shell. Related Links Application Shells An application shell is a module used to initialize and run an application (Windows or character-based) or application server. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}